Here’s a minimal example of what I’m working on:
```
extern crate MyTrait;
pub struct X<'a> {
pub fn method(&self) {}
};
impl MyTrait for X<'a> {
    fn foo(&self, y: &Y<'b>) { ... }
}```
What’s wrong with it? The error points to the impl block.

Here's the code I saw in the repo:
struct MyStruct<'a> {
    data: &'a str,
}
impl<'a> MyStruct<'a> {
    fn get(&self) -> &'a str {
        &self.data
    }
}
What's wrong with this? It compiles but I feel like it shouldn’t.

